ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Silent Spell|TYPE:Metamagic.Wizard|DESC:A silent spell can be cast with no verbal components. Spells without verbal components are not affected. A silent spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell's actual level.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Spell Penetration|TYPE:General.EpicWizard.CosmicDescryer|DESC:You get a +2 bonus on caster level checks (1d20 + caster level) made to overcome a creature's spell resistance.
ABILITY:FEAT|TYPE:NORMAL|CATEGORY:FEAT|KEY:Subdual Substitution|TYPE:Metamagic|DESC:When employing a spell with the acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic designator, you can modify the spell to deal subdual damage instead of the indicated type of energy damage.
